     <div class="bd"> 
      <ul class="newsNav"> 
       <li class="active" data-type="both">英汉对照<i></i></li> 
       <li data-type="cn">译文<i></i></li> 
       <li data-type="en">原文<i></i></li> 
      </ul> 
      <div class="newsCon"> 
       <div class="all"> 
        <p class="en"> <img src="http://s3-ec.buzzfed.com/static/2014-05/enhanced/webdr08/7/17/enhanced-buzz-29280-1399498474-63.jpg" /> </p>
        <p class="en">Miami Heat forward LeBron James and guard Norris Cole. &copy; Usa Today Sports / Reuters / Reuters</p>
        <p class="cn">迈阿密热火队的前锋勒布朗&middot;詹姆斯和后卫诺里斯-科尔。&copy;今日美国体育/路透社</p>
        <p class="en">Now that NBC has locked up television rights for the Olympics through 2032, the NBA league contract that expires in two years is basically the only major sports rights package available before 2020. That means the NBA has a strong negotiating position in the marketplace as its television contract gets close to an expiration date.</p>
        <p class="cn">现在，nbc已经锁定奥运会电视转播权通过2032，nba联赛的合同，在两年期满后基本上是唯一的主要的体育权利的封装前2020。这意味着nba有很强的谈判地位，在市场上为其电视合约接近到期日。</p>
        <p class="en">“The NBA’s television contract is coming up at a favorable time in the cycle,” said Marc Ganis, president of Sports Corp Limited, noting that professional football, baseball, and hockey, as well as college football, all signed new long-term national television rights deals in recent years. “There are more networks in the marketplace that need NBA games than will get them.”</p>
        <p class="cn">“nba的电视转播合同即将在循环中的一个有利的时间，说：”马克&middot;甘尼斯，体育集团有限公司主席，并指出，职业足球，棒球，曲棍球，以及大学足球，都签订了新的长期的国家的电视转播权交易近年来。“在需要nba比赛比市场上有更多的网络将得到他们。”</p>
        <p class="en">Put more simply, the NBA is going to get paid.</p>
        <p class="cn">简单地说，在nba会得到报酬。</p>
        <p class="en"> <img src="http://s3-ec.buzzfed.com/static/2014-05/enhanced/webdr03/7/17/enhanced-4463-1399498603-1.jpg" /> </p>
        <p class="en">Comcast CEO Brian Roberts and IOC President Thomas Bach Via <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.olympic.org/news/ioc-awards-olympic-games-broadcast-rights-to-nbcuniversal-through-to-2032/230995" target="_blank">olympic.org</a> </p>
        <p class="cn">康卡斯特首席执行官布瑞恩罗伯茨和国际奥委会主席托马斯巴赫通过 <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.olympic.org/news/ioc-awards-olympic-games-broadcast-rights-to-nbcuniversal-through-to-2032/230995" target="_blank">olympic.org</a> </p>
        <p class="en">NBC’s Olympics deal caught industry observers flat-footed with the surprise announcement Wednesday. NBC, which is owned by cable giant Comcast, and the International Olympic Committee said that they were extending their U.S. television rights deal for six Olympic events beginning in 2021 through 2032. NBC is paying $7.65 billion in total, or $1.275 billion for each games, for the U.S. broadcast, cable, internet, and mobile rights, along with an additional $100 million signing bonus to promote the games that take place between 2015 and 2020.</p>
        <p class="cn">nbc的奥运处理引起业界观察家措手不及的惊喜星期三的声明。美国全国广播公司，是由拥有有线电视巨头comcast，和国际奥委会说他们扩展他们的美国电视转播权协议六奥运会开始在2021到2032。美国全国广播公司总共支付了7650000000美元，或1275000000美元每游戏，美国广播，有线电视，互联网，移动的权利，以及额外的100000000美元的签约奖金促使发生2015和2020之间的游戏。</p>
        <p class="en">NBC previously paid just under $10 billion combined over several deals to broadcast the Olympics from 2000 to 2020. With Wednesday’s deal, the network will stand as the sole U.S. broadcast home for the first three decades of the new century.</p>
        <p class="cn">nbc先前支付10000000000美元的组合在几个交易转播奥运会从2000到2020。星期三的交易中，网络将成为唯一的美国广播家新世纪的第一个三年。</p>
        <p class="en">Steve Burke, NBC’s Chief Executive, <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.olympic.org/news/ioc-awards-olympic-games-broadcast-rights-to-nbcuniversal-through-to-2032/230995" target="_blank">called the Olympics</a> “part of the fabric of our company” in announcing the deal. He also called them “massively popular and profitable programming,” which is only partially true. While the Olympics are indeed a huge ratings draw, they aren’t always profitable. For instance, NBC lost $223 million on the 2010 Vancouver games and only eked out a slight profit on the 2012 London games. Burke said during <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/nbcuniversal-first-quarter-financials-rise-698079" target="_blank">Comcast’s first-quarter earnings call</a> last month that the Sochi games were profitable, but he didn’t provide an exact figure.</p>
        <p class="cn">史提夫伯克，nbc的首席执行官， <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.olympic.org/news/ioc-awards-olympic-games-broadcast-rights-to-nbcuniversal-through-to-2032/230995" target="_blank">called the olympics</a> ”在宣布交易的公司”的一部分。他还称他们为“大规模流行的和有利可图的规划，“这只是部分正确。而奥运会的确是一个巨大的收视率得出，他们并不总是有益的。例如，nbc损失在2010温哥华奥运会的223000000只维持在2012伦敦奥运会略有盈利。伯克在上个月 <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/nbcuniversal-first-quarter-financials-rise-698079" target="_blank">comcast’s first-quarter earnings call</a> 索契奥运会是有益的，但他没有提供一个确切的数字。</p>
        <p class="en">But for Comcast, the nation’s largest cable operator which generated more than $17 billion in revenue over the first three months of this year, the Olympics don’t need to be profitable. The company views the games as a promotional platform for the programming of NBC and its other networks, aiming to take advantage of the large viewership to attract new audiences to its regular programming. Indeed, in light of the proposed $45.2 billion offer to acquire Time Warner Cable, spending $7.65 billion on the Olympics is basically pocket change for Comcast.</p>
        <p class="cn">但对于comcast公司，美国最大的有线运营商的收入超过17000000000美元在今年前三个月，奥运会不需要赚钱。公司把奥运会作为全国广播公司和其他的网络编程的一个宣传平台，旨在利用大量的观众吸引新观众的节目。事实上，在所提出的45200000000美元收购时代华纳有线电视光，花费了7650000000美元在奥运会基本上是康卡斯特的零钱。</p>
        <p class="en">“It is hard to project anything reasonable financially with a deal that doesn’t start until eight years from now and ends 18 years from now,” Ganis said. “Clearly, they are making a bet using today’s money. It’s not a massive gamble for them. Even if they miss, they aren’t betting the company so it is a worthwhile deal for them to do.”</p>
        <p class="cn">“这是很难的项目的所有合理的金融交易，不能启动，直到八年后的现在，结束18年后的现在，“甘尼斯说。“显然，他们是用今天的钱打赌。对他们来说不是一个大的赌博。即使他们想，他们不是博彩公司是他们做的有价值的成果。”</p>
        <p class="en"> <img src="http://s3-ec.buzzfed.com/static/2014-05/enhanced/webdr02/7/17/enhanced-buzz-9529-1399498670-22.jpg" /> </p>
        <p class="en">San Antonio Spurs forward Tim Duncan and Dallas Mavericks guard Vince Carter. Ron Jenkins/Fort Worth Star-Telegram / MCT</p>
        <p class="cn">安东尼奥马刺队的前锋提姆邓肯和达拉斯小牛队的后卫文斯卡特。罗恩詹金斯/沃斯堡星电报/ mct</p>
        <p class="en">Wrapping up Olympics broadcast rights so early ― and for so long a timeframe ― underscores the immense value live sports programming has to television networks in a DVR and on-demand world. As one of the few programming areas that still attracts a massive audience to live broadcasts, televised sports in turn are attractive to advertisers.</p>
        <p class="cn">结束了奥运转播权这么早和如此长的时间――强调的巨大价值体育节目直播电视网络已在dvr和点播的世界。作为一个很少的编程领域，仍然吸引大量观众直播电视的体育节目，又能吸引广告商。</p>
        <p class="en">That’s why CBS, NBC, and FOX all created new national sports cable networks in the last few years, joining ESPN, Turner Broadcasting, and others; and it’s why a plethora of regional sports networks like YES have been born out of acquiring individual teams’ television rights. And that’s why the new NBA contract is expected to be huge for the league.</p>
        <p class="cn">这就是为什么cbs，nbc和福克斯，都创造了新的全国体育有线网络在过去的几年里，加入espn，特纳广播公司，和其他人；这就是为什么大量的区域体育网络像是已经出世了获取个人团队的电视转播权。这就是为什么新的nba合同预计将巨大的联盟。</p>
        <p class="en">The NBA’s <a rel="nofollow" href="http://adage.com/article/media/nba-double-rights-fees-tv-deals/241839/" target="_blank">current contract</a> , which expires at the end of the 2015C2016 season, was negotiated eight years ago, well before the rise of digital and mobile video and the abundance of buyers competing for sports rights. Under the previous deal, ESPN/ABC and Turner, the league’s current television partners, paid the NBA around $930 million per year.</p>
        <p class="cn">在nba的 <a rel="nofollow" href="http://adage.com/article/media/nba-double-rights-fees-tv-deals/241839/" target="_blank">current contract</a> ，它将在2015C2016赛季结束，谈判是八年前，在数字和移动视频和买家竞争的体育权利的丰度上升。先前的协议下，espn和abc和特纳，联盟目前的电视合作伙伴，nba支付每年930000000美元左右。</p>
        <p class="en">Sources involved with or close to the situation told BuzzFeed that the NBA and its partners are currently having “very informal” discussions about a new deal and a renewal isn’t imminent. Reports previously said the NBA wanted to sign a new deal by the end of this summer. These sources said the NBA is looking at a $2 billion annual payment and a shorter timeframe than the previous deal to keep its television rights off-cycle ― meaning not competing ― with the other major sports networks.</p>
        <p class="cn">有关消息或接近的情况告诉buzzfeed合作，nba及其合作伙伴正在“非正式”讨论了新的交易和更新不是迫在眉睫。报告先前说，nba想在今年夏天签下新合同。这些人士说，nba在每年2000000000美元的支付和更短的时间比保持其电视转播权的非周期-前处理的意义不竞争与其他主要体育网。</p>
        <p class="en">Ganis said a $2 billion annual figure is not unreasonable. Indeed, he expects the NBA to secure an increase of between 90% and 125% in its new deal, which would rank it as the largest percentage increase for a major sports league television rights package in the U.S. The NFL secured a roughly 70% annual increase in its new television deals, but of course the overall value was unprecedented given the league’s huge ratings and appeal, with four networks ― CBS, NBC, FOX, and ESPN ― paying a <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sportsbusinessdaily.com/Journal/Issues/2014/02/10/Media/NFL-CBS.aspx" target="_blank">collective $43 billion</a> to broadcast NFL games from 2014C2022.</p>
        <p class="cn">甘尼斯说，2000000000美元的年度人物是不合理的。事实上，他认为nba确保新协议的90%和125%之间的增加，这将把它作为一个主要的体育赛事电视转播权包在美国橄榄球固定在其新的电视转播协议，约70%的年增长率增加最大，但当然总体价值是前所未有的了联赛的高收视率和吸引力，四网络cbs，nbc，狐狸，和espn支付一 <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sportsbusinessdaily.com/journal/issues/2014/02/10/media/nfl-cbs.aspx" target="_blank">collective $43 billion</a> 播放橄榄球比赛从2014C2022。</p>
        <p class="en">ESPN/ABC and Turner have an exclusive negotiating window with the NBA. Should they not reach a deal, which sources said is unlikely, the league could open up the process to other bidders. A more likely scenario, however, is that the NBA and its current partners negotiate a new deal and the league carves out a new programming package akin to what the NFL did with the addition of Thursday night games to maximize revenue and bring in a new partner.</p>
        <p class="cn">espn和abc和特纳独家谈判的窗口与nba。如果他们不能达成协议，该人士说是不可能的，联盟将开放过程中对其他投标人。然而，更可能的情况是，，，nba和其目前的合作伙伴谈判新的交易和联盟开辟了新的类似于nfl星期四晚上会有收益的最大化，带来一个新的合作伙伴加入的程序包。</p>
        <p class="en">Mark Lazarus, chairman of NBC Sports, said at a recent conference when asked about the network’s interest in acquiring NBA rights: “They are in relationships right now with other partners, but if the opportunity were to arise, certainly we would talk with them as we are all old friends.”</p>
        <p class="cn">马克说，nbc体育主席说，在最近的一次会议上，当被问及在nba的权利获取网络的兴趣：“他们的关系，现在与其他合作伙伴，但如果有机会出现，我们当然可以与他们交谈，我们都是老朋友了。”</p>
        <p class="en">Representatives for the NBA, NBC, and ESPN declined to comment for this story.</p>
        <p class="cn">代表的nba，nbc，和espn拒绝对此发表评论。</p> 
       </div> 
       <div class="cn undis"> 
        <p><img src="http://s3-ec.buzzfed.com/static/2014-05/enhanced/webdr08/7/17/enhanced-buzz-29280-1399498474-63.jpg" /></p>
        <p>迈阿密热火队的前锋勒布朗&middot;詹姆斯和后卫诺里斯-科尔。&copy;今日美国体育/路透社</p>
        <p>现在，nbc已经锁定奥运会电视转播权通过2032，nba联赛的合同，在两年期满后基本上是唯一的主要的体育权利的封装前2020。这意味着nba有很强的谈判地位，在市场上为其电视合约接近到期日。</p>
        <p>“nba的电视转播合同即将在循环中的一个有利的时间，说：”马克&middot;甘尼斯，体育集团有限公司主席，并指出，职业足球，棒球，曲棍球，以及大学足球，都签订了新的长期的国家的电视转播权交易近年来。“在需要nba比赛比市场上有更多的网络将得到他们。”</p>
        <p>简单地说，在nba会得到报酬。</p>
        <p><img src="http://s3-ec.buzzfed.com/static/2014-05/enhanced/webdr03/7/17/enhanced-4463-1399498603-1.jpg" /></p>
        <p>康卡斯特首席执行官布瑞恩罗伯茨和国际奥委会主席托马斯巴赫通过<a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.olympic.org/news/ioc-awards-olympic-games-broadcast-rights-to-nbcuniversal-through-to-2032/230995" target="_blank">olympic.org</a></p>
        <p>nbc的奥运处理引起业界观察家措手不及的惊喜星期三的声明。美国全国广播公司，是由拥有有线电视巨头comcast，和国际奥委会说他们扩展他们的美国电视转播权协议六奥运会开始在2021到2032。美国全国广播公司总共支付了7650000000美元，或1275000000美元每游戏，美国广播，有线电视，互联网，移动的权利，以及额外的100000000美元的签约奖金促使发生2015和2020之间的游戏。</p>
        <p>nbc先前支付10000000000美元的组合在几个交易转播奥运会从2000到2020。星期三的交易中，网络将成为唯一的美国广播家新世纪的第一个三年。</p>
        <p>史提夫伯克，nbc的首席执行官，<a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.olympic.org/news/ioc-awards-olympic-games-broadcast-rights-to-nbcuniversal-through-to-2032/230995" target="_blank">called the olympics</a>”在宣布交易的公司”的一部分。他还称他们为“大规模流行的和有利可图的规划，“这只是部分正确。而奥运会的确是一个巨大的收视率得出，他们并不总是有益的。例如，nbc损失在2010温哥华奥运会的223000000只维持在2012伦敦奥运会略有盈利。伯克在上个月<a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/nbcuniversal-first-quarter-financials-rise-698079" target="_blank">comcast’s first-quarter earnings call</a>索契奥运会是有益的，但他没有提供一个确切的数字。</p>
        <p>但对于comcast公司，美国最大的有线运营商的收入超过17000000000美元在今年前三个月，奥运会不需要赚钱。公司把奥运会作为全国广播公司和其他的网络编程的一个宣传平台，旨在利用大量的观众吸引新观众的节目。事实上，在所提出的45200000000美元收购时代华纳有线电视光，花费了7650000000美元在奥运会基本上是康卡斯特的零钱。</p>
        <p>“这是很难的项目的所有合理的金融交易，不能启动，直到八年后的现在，结束18年后的现在，“甘尼斯说。“显然，他们是用今天的钱打赌。对他们来说不是一个大的赌博。即使他们想，他们不是博彩公司是他们做的有价值的成果。”</p>
        <p><img src="http://s3-ec.buzzfed.com/static/2014-05/enhanced/webdr02/7/17/enhanced-buzz-9529-1399498670-22.jpg" /></p>
        <p>安东尼奥马刺队的前锋提姆邓肯和达拉斯小牛队的后卫文斯卡特。罗恩詹金斯/沃斯堡星电报/ mct</p>
        <p>结束了奥运转播权这么早和如此长的时间――强调的巨大价值体育节目直播电视网络已在dvr和点播的世界。作为一个很少的编程领域，仍然吸引大量观众直播电视的体育节目，又能吸引广告商。</p>
        <p>这就是为什么cbs，nbc和福克斯，都创造了新的全国体育有线网络在过去的几年里，加入espn，特纳广播公司，和其他人；这就是为什么大量的区域体育网络像是已经出世了获取个人团队的电视转播权。这就是为什么新的nba合同预计将巨大的联盟。</p>
        <p>在nba的<a rel="nofollow" href="http://adage.com/article/media/nba-double-rights-fees-tv-deals/241839/" target="_blank">current contract</a>，它将在2015C2016赛季结束，谈判是八年前，在数字和移动视频和买家竞争的体育权利的丰度上升。先前的协议下，espn和abc和特纳，联盟目前的电视合作伙伴，nba支付每年930000000美元左右。</p>
        <p>有关消息或接近的情况告诉buzzfeed合作，nba及其合作伙伴正在“非正式”讨论了新的交易和更新不是迫在眉睫。报告先前说，nba想在今年夏天签下新合同。这些人士说，nba在每年2000000000美元的支付和更短的时间比保持其电视转播权的非周期-前处理的意义不竞争与其他主要体育网。</p>
        <p>甘尼斯说，2000000000美元的年度人物是不合理的。事实上，他认为nba确保新协议的90%和125%之间的增加，这将把它作为一个主要的体育赛事电视转播权包在美国橄榄球固定在其新的电视转播协议，约70%的年增长率增加最大，但当然总体价值是前所未有的了联赛的高收视率和吸引力，四网络cbs，nbc，狐狸，和espn支付一<a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sportsbusinessdaily.com/journal/issues/2014/02/10/media/nfl-cbs.aspx" target="_blank">collective $43 billion</a>播放橄榄球比赛从2014C2022。</p>
        <p>espn和abc和特纳独家谈判的窗口与nba。如果他们不能达成协议，该人士说是不可能的，联盟将开放过程中对其他投标人。然而，更可能的情况是，，，nba和其目前的合作伙伴谈判新的交易和联盟开辟了新的类似于nfl星期四晚上会有收益的最大化，带来一个新的合作伙伴加入的程序包。</p>
        <p>马克说，nbc体育主席说，在最近的一次会议上，当被问及在nba的权利获取网络的兴趣：“他们的关系，现在与其他合作伙伴，但如果有机会出现，我们当然可以与他们交谈，我们都是老朋友了。”</p>
        <p>代表的nba，nbc，和espn拒绝对此发表评论。</p> 
       </div> 
       <div class="en undis"> 
        <p><img src="http://s3-ec.buzzfed.com/static/2014-05/enhanced/webdr08/7/17/enhanced-buzz-29280-1399498474-63.jpg" /></p>
        <p>Miami Heat forward LeBron James and guard Norris Cole. &copy; Usa Today Sports / Reuters / Reuters</p>
        <p>Now that NBC has locked up television rights for the Olympics through 2032, the NBA league contract that expires in two years is basically the only major sports rights package available before 2020. That means the NBA has a strong negotiating position in the marketplace as its television contract gets close to an expiration date.</p>
        <p>“The NBA’s television contract is coming up at a favorable time in the cycle,” said Marc Ganis, president of Sports Corp Limited, noting that professional football, baseball, and hockey, as well as college football, all signed new long-term national television rights deals in recent years. “There are more networks in the marketplace that need NBA games than will get them.”</p>
        <p>Put more simply, the NBA is going to get paid.</p>
        <p><img src="http://s3-ec.buzzfed.com/static/2014-05/enhanced/webdr03/7/17/enhanced-4463-1399498603-1.jpg" /></p>
        <p>Comcast CEO Brian Roberts and IOC President Thomas Bach Via <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.olympic.org/news/ioc-awards-olympic-games-broadcast-rights-to-nbcuniversal-through-to-2032/230995" target="_blank">olympic.org</a></p>
        <p>NBC’s Olympics deal caught industry observers flat-footed with the surprise announcement Wednesday. NBC, which is owned by cable giant Comcast, and the International Olympic Committee said that they were extending their U.S. television rights deal for six Olympic events beginning in 2021 through 2032. NBC is paying $7.65 billion in total, or $1.275 billion for each games, for the U.S. broadcast, cable, internet, and mobile rights, along with an additional $100 million signing bonus to promote the games that take place between 2015 and 2020.</p>
        <p>NBC previously paid just under $10 billion combined over several deals to broadcast the Olympics from 2000 to 2020. With Wednesday’s deal, the network will stand as the sole U.S. broadcast home for the first three decades of the new century.</p>
        <p>Steve Burke, NBC’s Chief Executive, <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.olympic.org/news/ioc-awards-olympic-games-broadcast-rights-to-nbcuniversal-through-to-2032/230995" target="_blank">called the Olympics</a> “part of the fabric of our company” in announcing the deal. He also called them “massively popular and profitable programming,” which is only partially true. While the Olympics are indeed a huge ratings draw, they aren’t always profitable. For instance, NBC lost $223 million on the 2010 Vancouver games and only eked out a slight profit on the 2012 London games. Burke said during <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/nbcuniversal-first-quarter-financials-rise-698079" target="_blank">Comcast’s first-quarter earnings call</a> last month that the Sochi games were profitable, but he didn’t provide an exact figure.</p>
        <p>But for Comcast, the nation’s largest cable operator which generated more than $17 billion in revenue over the first three months of this year, the Olympics don’t need to be profitable. The company views the games as a promotional platform for the programming of NBC and its other networks, aiming to take advantage of the large viewership to attract new audiences to its regular programming. Indeed, in light of the proposed $45.2 billion offer to acquire Time Warner Cable, spending $7.65 billion on the Olympics is basically pocket change for Comcast.</p>
        <p>“It is hard to project anything reasonable financially with a deal that doesn’t start until eight years from now and ends 18 years from now,” Ganis said. “Clearly, they are making a bet using today’s money. It’s not a massive gamble for them. Even if they miss, they aren’t betting the company so it is a worthwhile deal for them to do.”</p>
        <p><img src="http://s3-ec.buzzfed.com/static/2014-05/enhanced/webdr02/7/17/enhanced-buzz-9529-1399498670-22.jpg" /></p>
        <p>San Antonio Spurs forward Tim Duncan and Dallas Mavericks guard Vince Carter. Ron Jenkins/Fort Worth Star-Telegram / MCT</p>
        <p>Wrapping up Olympics broadcast rights so early ― and for so long a timeframe ― underscores the immense value live sports programming has to television networks in a DVR and on-demand world. As one of the few programming areas that still attracts a massive audience to live broadcasts, televised sports in turn are attractive to advertisers.</p>
        <p>That’s why CBS, NBC, and FOX all created new national sports cable networks in the last few years, joining ESPN, Turner Broadcasting, and others; and it’s why a plethora of regional sports networks like YES have been born out of acquiring individual teams’ television rights. And that’s why the new NBA contract is expected to be huge for the league.</p>
        <p>The NBA’s <a rel="nofollow" href="http://adage.com/article/media/nba-double-rights-fees-tv-deals/241839/" target="_blank">current contract</a>, which expires at the end of the 2015C2016 season, was negotiated eight years ago, well before the rise of digital and mobile video and the abundance of buyers competing for sports rights. Under the previous deal, ESPN/ABC and Turner, the league’s current television partners, paid the NBA around $930 million per year.</p>
        <p>Sources involved with or close to the situation told BuzzFeed that the NBA and its partners are currently having “very informal” discussions about a new deal and a renewal isn’t imminent. Reports previously said the NBA wanted to sign a new deal by the end of this summer. These sources said the NBA is looking at a $2 billion annual payment and a shorter timeframe than the previous deal to keep its television rights off-cycle ― meaning not competing ― with the other major sports networks.</p>
        <p>Ganis said a $2 billion annual figure is not unreasonable. Indeed, he expects the NBA to secure an increase of between 90% and 125% in its new deal, which would rank it as the largest percentage increase for a major sports league television rights package in the U.S. The NFL secured a roughly 70% annual increase in its new television deals, but of course the overall value was unprecedented given the league’s huge ratings and appeal, with four networks ― CBS, NBC, FOX, and ESPN ― paying a <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.sportsbusinessdaily.com/Journal/Issues/2014/02/10/Media/NFL-CBS.aspx" target="_blank">collective $43 billion</a> to broadcast NFL games from 2014C2022.</p>
        <p>ESPN/ABC and Turner have an exclusive negotiating window with the NBA. Should they not reach a deal, which sources said is unlikely, the league could open up the process to other bidders. A more likely scenario, however, is that the NBA and its current partners negotiate a new deal and the league carves out a new programming package akin to what the NFL did with the addition of Thursday night games to maximize revenue and bring in a new partner.</p>
        <p>Mark Lazarus, chairman of NBC Sports, said at a recent conference when asked about the network’s interest in acquiring NBA rights: “They are in relationships right now with other partners, but if the opportunity were to arise, certainly we would talk with them as we are all old friends.”</p>
        <p>Representatives for the NBA, NBC, and ESPN declined to comment for this story.</p> 
